<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=915&amp;p=8027#p8027"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Fredrik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />So if it needs 100ns isn't that only 10Kb/s witch should be possible to achive?<br /></div><br /><br />In hardware, sure.  Software, I dunno.  You'd have to send the address/control (and data for writes) to the PC, then have the PC process that, and return the data in time.  And if you want CHR-ROM this way, then you'd have to do the same for CHR.<br /><br />I can't say it's impossible, but it sounds pretty difficult.  I don't know if I figured this right, but 1.789Mhz + 2.68Mhz with a memory access on every cycle I think would be 4,469,000 bytes per second.  Then maybe quadruple that to include all address and control signals.  Is that right?  That's a lot more than 10kb/s.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Jan 07, 2006 2:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
